item.title: Anything, Not Everything
item.description: A reocurring concern as a developing software engineer (SWE) is the notion that one must know everything. This is misleading; I openly admit that I don't know everything. I don't have enough time to master each and every aspect of the programming involved, no one does. The demonstration of our web development expertise is to efficiently and effectively identify where to locate information and become proficient in the current role. I know where to find anything so that I do not need to know everything.
